07/10/2002
KORCE, Albania -- Defence Minister Pandeli Majko and Minister of Agriculture Agron Duka opened the first rural trade centre in the country on Sunday (6 October). Local authorities in Korce built the centre with the financial assistance of the Swedish International Development Agency. The agency is financing nine other projects and plans to launch 12 more. The new facility aims to boost retail and wholesale trade with livestock and food products and to help producers improve their distribution channels.
In other news, the Albanian government has signed a contract with the Italian company Essegei for the upgrade of 25 small hydroelectric power plants. The Italians will invest $8m from 2002 to 2006 to put the plants back in operation. (ATA - 06/10/02; AP - 04/10/02)
